<db:para><db:emphasis>Right to Left</db:emphasis> is a collection of small QML examples relating to right to left (RTL) localization support. For more information, visit <db:link xlink:href="qtquick-positioning-righttoleft.xml">Right-to-left User Interfaces</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>These are the examples in Right to Left:</db:para>
<db:itemizedlist>
<db:listitem>
<db:para><db:emphasis>Layout Direction</db:emphasis> - shows RTL layout direction</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para><db:emphasis>Layout Mirroring</db:emphasis> - shows automatic mirroring of horizontal layouts in RTL locales</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para><db:emphasis>Text Alignment</db:emphasis> - shows automatic mirroring of text alignment in RTL locales</db:para>
</db:listitem>
</db:itemizedlist>
<db:section xml:id="running-the-example">
<db:title>Running the Example</db:title>
<db:para>To run the example from <db:link xlink:href="http://doc.qt.io/qtcreator/index.html">Qt Creator</db:link>, open the <db:emphasis role="bold">Welcome</db:emphasis> mode and select the example from <db:emphasis role="bold">Examples</db:emphasis>. For more information, visit <db:link xlink:href="http://doc.qt.io/qtcreator/creator-build-example-application.html">Building and Running an Example</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
